{"title_page": "Velloor Perunthatta Siva Temple", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{short description|Hindu temple in India}}\n{{Infobox Mandir\n| name               = Velloor Perunthatta Siva Temple\n| image              = File:\u0d2a\u0d46\u0d30\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f_\u0d2e\u0d39\u0d3e\u0d26\u0d47\u0d35\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d37\u0d47\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02.jpg\n| alt                = \n| caption            = Main Entrance\n| map_type           = <!-- India Kerala -->\n| map_caption        = Location in Kerala\n| coordinates        = {{coord|8.555207|76.961195|type:landmark_region:IN|display=inline,title}} \n| other_names        = \n| country            = {{Flag|India}}\n| state              = [[Kerala]]\n| district           = [[Kottayam District|Kottayam]]\n| location           = [[Velloor]], [[Thalayolaparambu]]\n| elevation_m        = \n| deity              = [[Shiva]]\n| festivals          = [[Maha Shivaratri]] \n| architecture       = [[Architecture of Kerala|Kerala style]]\n| temple_quantity    = \n| monument_quantity  = 1\n| inscriptions       = \n| year_completed     = Not known\n| creator            = \n| website            =\n}}\n\n''' Velloor Perunthatta Siva Temple ''' is located at [[Velloor]], near to [[Thalayolaparambu]] in [[Kottayam district]]. The presiding deity of the [[temple]] is [[Shiva]], located in separate sanctum sanatoriums, facing east.<ref>{{cite web\n| title = 108 Siva Temples \n| url = http://www.thekeralatemples.com/knowmore/108_siva_temples.htm\n| accessdate = }}\n</ref> It is believed that this temple is one of the 108 Shiva temples of Kerala and is installed by sage [[Parasurama]] dedicated to [[Shiva]].<ref>{{cite book |title=108 Siva Kshetrangal |author=Kunjikuttan Ilayath |publisher=H and C Books}}{{page needed|date=October 2018}}</ref><ref>https://www.sanskritimagazine.com/indian-religions/hinduism/108-shiva-temples-created-lord-parasurama-kerala/</ref> It is one of the oldest Shiva temple in Kottayam District.\n\n==See also==\n* [[108 Shiva Temples]]\n* [[Temples of Kerala]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Hindu temples in Kerala}}\n\n[[Category:108 Siva Temples]]\n[[Category:Shiva temples in Kerala]]\n[[Category:Hindu temples in Kottayam district]]\n\n\n{{hindu-temple-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{short description|Hindu temple in India}}\n{{Infobox Mandir\n| name               = Velloor Perunthatta Siva Temple\n| image              = File:\u0d2a\u0d46\u0d30\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f_\u0d2e\u0d39\u0d3e\u0d26\u0d47\u0d35\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d37\u0d47\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02.jpg\n| alt                = \n| caption            = Main Entrance\n| map_type           = <!-- India Kerala -->\n| map_caption        = Location in Kerala\n| coordinates        = {{coord|8.555207|76.961195|type:landmark_region:IN|display=inline,title}} \n| other_names        = \n| country            = {{Flag|India}}\n| state              = [[Kerala]]\n| district           = [[Kottayam District|Kottayam]]\n| location           = [[Velloor]], [[Thalayolaparambu]]\n| elevation_m        = \n| deity              = [[Shiva]]\n| festivals          = [[Maha Shivaratri]] \n| architecture       = [[Architecture of Kerala|Kerala style]]\n| temple_quantity    = \n| monument_quantity  = 1\n| inscriptions       = \n| year_completed     = Not known\n| creator            = \n| website            =\n}}\n\n''' Velloor Perunthatta Siva Temple ''' is located at [[Velloor]], near to [[Thalayolaparambu]] in [[Kottayam district]]. The presiding deity of the [[temple]] is [[Lord Shiva]], located in separate sanctum sanatoriums, facing east.<ref>{{cite web\n| title = 108 Siva Temples \n| url = http://www.thekeralatemples.com/knowmore/108_siva_temples.htm\n| accessdate = }}\n</ref> It is believed that this temple is one of the 108 Shiva temples of Kerala and is installed by sage [[Parasurama]] dedicated to [[Lord Shiva]].<ref>{{cite book |title=108 Siva Kshetrangal |author=Kunjikuttan Ilayath |publisher=H and C Books}}{{page needed|date=October 2018}}</ref><ref>https://www.sanskritimagazine.com/indian-religions/hinduism/108-shiva-temples-created-lord-parasurama-kerala/</ref> It is one of the oldest Shiva temple in Kottayam District.\n\n==See also==\n* [[108 Shiva Temples]]\n* [[Temples of Kerala]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Hindu temples in Kerala}}\n\n[[Category:108 Siva Temples]]\n[[Category:Shiva temples in Kerala]]\n[[Category:Hindu temples in Kottayam district]]\n\n\n{{hindu-temple-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Velloor_Perunthatta_Siva_Temple"}
{"title_page": "Trans Sarbagita", "text_new": "{{Infobox Public transit\n| name = Trans Sarbagita\n| image =Trans Sarbagita bus.JPG\n| imagesize =200px\n| locale = [[Denpasar]], [[Bali]], [[Indonesia]]\n| transit_type = [[bus rapid transit]]\n| began_operation = 18 August 2011\n| system_length = 42 Km\n| lines = 4 (operation), 13 (planned)\n| stations = 31 Stations\n| ridership = 5,000 passengers per day\n| website = [http://www.dishubinkom.baliprov.go.id/id/ANGKUTAN-UMUM-Trans-SARBAGITA][https://feedersarbagitadps.wordpress.com/]\n}}\n[[File:Sarbagita Halte Bualu 1.JPG|thumb|Bus Stop \"Bualu 1\" in Bali, Indonesia.]]\n'''Trans Sarbagita''' is a [[bus rapid transit]] (BRT) system in [[Denpasar]], [[Bali]], [[Indonesia]]. The system began its operations on 18 August 2011. It was designed to rebuild Bali's public transport system. As of 2014, the buses carried 5,000 passengers per day with 25 Buses in operation. The buses run in 2 routes, the first is Batubulan - Nusa Dua vv and Denpasar Kota - [[Garuda Wisnu Kencana]] vv. The ticket prices are 3,500 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for adults and 2,500 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for students. in 2015 Trans Sarbagita launched two new routes, Tabanan-Mengwi-[[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bandara]] and Mahendradata-Sanur-Lebih.<ref>{{cite web|title=ANGKUTAN UMUM Trans SARBAGITA|url=http://www.dishubinkom.baliprov.go.id/id/ANGKUTAN-UMUM-Trans-SARBAGITA|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Routes ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Corridor !! Route\n|-\n| 1 || [[Ngurah Rai Stadium | Kota]] - [[Garuda Wisnu Kencana]]\n|-\n| 2 || Batubulan - Sentral Parkir Kuta - [[Nusa Dua]]\n|-\n| 3 || [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - Renon - Petitenget\n|-\n| 4 || Batubulan - Jl. Gatot Subroto - [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bandara]]\n|-\n| 5 || [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - Kedewatan - [[Ubud]]\n|-\n| 6 || [[Mengwi]] - [[Ngurah Rai Stadium | Kota]] - Benoa Harbour\n|-\n| 7 || [[Tabanan Regency | Tabanan]]  - [[Mengwi]] - [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bandara]]\n|-\n| 8 || Sentral Parkir Kuta - [[Tanah Lot]]\n|-\n| 9 || Batubulan - [[Ngurah Rai Stadium | Kota]] - Sentral Parkir Kuta\n|-\n| 10 || [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bandara]] - [[Nusa Dua]]\n|-\n| 11 || Mahendradata - [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - Lebih Beach\n|-\n| 12 || [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - [[Ngurah Rai Stadium | Kota]] - [[Canggu]]\n|-\n| 13 || [[Gianyar Regency | Gianyar]] - [[Mengwi]] - [[Tabanan Regency | Tabanan]]\n|-\n| 14 || Ubung - Buluh Indah - Sentral Parkir Kuta\n|-\n| 15 || [[Mengwi]] - [[Dalung, Kuta Utara | Dalung]] - Batubulan\n|-\n| 16 || Tegal - Mambal\n|-\n| 17 || [[Mengwi]] - Darmasaba - Batubulan\n|}\nIn terminus like batubulan, passenger can switch to another buses or minibuses to other destinations such as [[Bangli Regency | Bangli]], [[Kintamani, Bali | Kintamani]], [[Karangasem Regency | Karangasem]], [[Klungkung Regency | Klungkung]]\n\n== Feeder ==\n\nTrans Sarbagita has seven feeder services that continue on the narrow roads and connect to the main bus corridors. There are three services in the Badung Regency, and four services in Denpasar city. The ticket prices are 3,000 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for adults and 2,000 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for students in C1, F1 and F2. 8,000 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for adults and 2,000 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for students in TP 01, TP 02, TP 03 and TP 04.<ref>{{cite web|title=Website Feeder Kota Denpasar|url=https://feedersarbagitadps.wordpress.com/ |accessdate=21 July 2016}}</ref>. In 2015, the feeder services in Denpasar city is suspended due to low ridership.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Feeder !! Route !! Fleet Colours\n|-\n| S1 || Tegal - Sentral Parkir Kuta - [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bandara]] || Dark Blue\n|-\n| F1 || [[Tanjung Benoa]] - [[Garuda Wisnu Kencana]] || White and Green\n|-\n| F2 || Kedonganan - [[Garuda Wisnu Kencana]] - [[Uluwatu, Bali | Uluwatu]] || White and Green\n|-\n| TP 01 || [[Ngurah Rai Stadium | Kota]] - Renon - Jl. Sudirman || Light Green\n|-\n| TP 02 || [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - Jl.Simpang Enam Teuku Umar || Light Green\n|-\n| TP 03 || Jl.Nias (RS Sanglah) - Jl.Simpang Enam Teuku Umar - Pemogan - Jl. P.Kawe - Jl.Nias (RS Sanglah) || Light Green\n|-\n| TP 04 || Jl.Sudirman - Jl.Waturenggong - Sidakarya || Light Green\n|}\n\n== Minibus (Non Feeder) Denpasar ==\n\n[[Share taxi|Angkot]] services other than feeder services is also exist in Denpasar City. they operated and owned mostly by driver itself and the service is not integrated to Trans Sarbagita since the feeder service is suspended. \n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Feeder !! Route !! Fleet colours\n|-\n| A || Kereneng - Sanur - Semawang || Green\n|-\n| E || Kereneng - Jl.Teuku Umar - Jl.Gatot Subroto - Jl.A.Yani - Kereneng || Light Yellow\n|-\n| F || Kereneng - Nitimandala Renon - Jl.Teuku Umar - Jl.Gatot Subroto - Jl.Nangka - Kereneng || Light Yellow and Red\n|-\n| G || Tegal Bus Station - Jl.Teuku Umar - Gemeh - Nitimandala Renon - Sanur - Semawang || Dark Blue and White\n|-\n| L || Gunung Agung Bus Station - Padang Indah Monang-Maning || Orange\n|-\n| S4 || Suci - Pesanggaran - Benoa Harbour || Grey\n|-\n| S7 || Suci - Sidakarya - Suwung Kangin - Semawang || Grey and Yellow\n|-\n| S8 || Suci - Pesanggaran - Benoa Harbour - Suwung Kauh Via Bypass Ngurah Rai || Grey and Green\n|-\n| UK || Ubung Bus Station - Kereneng || Blue and Red\n|-\n| US || Ubung Bus Station - RS Sanglah || Blue and Yellow\n|-\n| KS || Kereneng - RS Sanglah || Blue and Black\n|-\n| UT || Ubung Bus Station - Tegal Bus Station || Green\n|}\n\n== Fleet ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Operator !! Fleet\n|-\n| [[Perum DAMRI]] <br> || [[Mitsubishi Fuso Truck and Bus Corporation|Mitsubishi Fuso]] FE 84BC\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{bus rapid transit}}\n{{Urban Transit in Indonesia}}\n\n[[Category:Bus rapid transit in Indonesia|Bali]]\n[[Category:2011 establishments in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Transport in Bali]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Public transit\n| name = Trans Sarbagita\n| image =Trans Sarbagita bus.JPG\n| imagesize =200px\n| locale = [[Denpasar]], [[Bali]], [[Indonesia]]\n| transit_type = [[bus rapid transit]]\n| began_operation = 18 August 2011\n| system_length = 42 Km\n| lines = 4 (operation), 13 (planned)\n| stations = 31 Stations\n| ridership = 5,000 passengers per day\n| website = [http://www.dishubinkom.baliprov.go.id/id/ANGKUTAN-UMUM-Trans-SARBAGITA][https://feedersarbagitadps.wordpress.com/]\n}}\n[[File:Sarbagita Halte Bualu 1.JPG|thumb|Bus Stop \"Bualu 1\" in Bali, Indonesia.]]\n'''Trans Sarbagita''' is a [[bus rapid transit]] (BRT) system in [[Denpasar]], [[Bali]], [[Indonesia]]. The system began its operations on 18 August 2011. It was designed to rebuild Bali's public transport system. As of 2014, the buses carried 5,000 passengers per day with 25 Buses in operation. The buses run in 2 routes, the first is Batubulan - Nusa Dua vv and Denpasar Kota - [[Garuda Wisnu Kencana]] vv. The ticket prices are 3,500 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for adults and 2,500 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for students. in 2015 Trans Sarbagita launched two new routes, Tabanan-Mengwi-[[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bandara]] and Mahendradata-Sanur-Lebih.<ref>{{cite web|title=ANGKUTAN UMUM Trans SARBAGITA|url=http://www.dishubinkom.baliprov.go.id/id/ANGKUTAN-UMUM-Trans-SARBAGITA|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Routes ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Corridor !! Route\n|-\n| 1 || [[Ngurah Rai Stadium | Kota]] - [[Garuda Wisnu Kencana]]\n|-\n| 2 || Batubulan - Sentral Parkir Kuta - [[Nusa Dua]]\n|-\n| 3 || [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - Renon - Petitenget\n|-\n| 4 || Batubulan - Jl. Gatot Subroto - [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bandara]]\n|-\n| 5 || [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - Kedewatan - [[Ubud]]\n|-\n| 6 || [[Mengwi]] - [[Ngurah Rai Stadium | Kota]] - Benoa Harbour\n|-\n| 7 || [[Tabanan Regency | Tabanan]]  - [[Mengwi]] - [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bandara]]\n|-\n| 8 || Sentral Parkir Kuta - [[Tanah Lot]]\n|-\n| 9 || Batubulan - [[Ngurah Rai Stadium | Kota]] - Sentral Parkir Kuta\n|-\n| 10 || [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bandara]] - [[Nusa Dua]]\n|-\n| 11 || Mahendradata - [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - Lebih Beach\n|-\n| 12 || [[Sanur, Bali | Sanur]] - [[Ngurah Rai Stadium | Kota]] - [[Canggu]]\n|-\n| 13 || [[Gianyar Regency | Gianyar]] - [[Mengwi]] - [[Tabanan Regency | Tabanan]]\n|-\n| 14 || Ubung - Buluh Indah - Sentral Parkir Kuta\n|-\n| 15 || [[Mengwi]] - [[Dalung, Kuta Utara | Dalung]] - Batubulan\n|-\n| 16 || Tegal - Mambal\n|-\n| 17 || [[Mengwi]] - Darmasaba - Batubulan\n|}\nIn terminus like batubulan, passenger can switch to another buses or minibuses to other destinations such as [[Bangli Regency | Bangli]], [[Kintamani, Bali | Kintamani]], [[Karangasem Regency | Karangasem]], [[Klungkung Regency | Klungkung]]\n\n== Feeder ==\n\nTrans Sarbagita has seven feeder services that continue on the narrow roads and connect to the main bus corridors. There are three services in the Badung Regency, and four services in Denpasar city. The ticket prices are 3,000 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for adults and 2,000 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for students in C1, F1 and F2. 8,000 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for adults and 2,000 [[Indonesian rupiah|IDR]] for students in TP 01, TP 02, TP 03 and TP 04.<ref>{{cite web|title=Website Feeder Kota Denpasar|url=https://feedersarbagitadps.wordpress.com/ |accessdate=21 July 2016}}</ref>. In 2015, the feeder services in Denpasar city is suspended due to low ridership.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Feeder !! Route !! Fleet Colours\n|-\n| S1 || Tegal - Sentral Parkir Kuta - [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bandara]] || Dark Blue\n|-\n| F1 || [[Tanjung Benoa]] - [[Garuda Wisnu Kencana]] || White and Green\n|-\n| F2 || Kedonganan - [[Garuda Wisnu Kencana]] - [[Uluwatu, Bali | Uluwatu]] || White and Green\n|-\n| TP 01 |