{"title_page": "December 2019 United States airstrikes in Iraq and Syria", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Short description|War event against Iraqi group Kata'ib Hezbollah}}\n{{Infobox military operation\n |name          = December 2019 United States airstrikes in Iraq and Syria\n |partof        = the American-led interventions [[American-led intervention in Iraq (2014\u2013present)|in Iraq]] and [[American-led intervention in the Syrian Civil War|Syria]] ([[Operation Inherent Resolve]]) and the [[2019\u201320 Persian Gulf crisis]]\n |image         = \n |image_upright = \n |alt           = \n |caption       = \n |scope         = \n |type          = [[Airstrike]]s\n| location  = [[Al Anbar Governorate|Anbar]] and [[Kirkuk Governorate|Kirkuk]], Iraq\n| location2 = Valley of [[Euphrates River]], Syria<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/29/world/middleeast/us-airstrikes-iran-iraq-syria.html U.S. Launches Airstrikes on Iranian-Backed Forces in Iraq and Syria] en: ''[[The New York Times]]''. Consultado el 29-12-2019.</ref>\n |coordinates   = \n |map_type      = \n |map_size      = \n |map_caption   = \n |map_label     = \n |planned       = \n |planned_by    = \n |commanded_by  = \n |objective     = \n |target        = {{flagicon image|Kata'ib Hezbollah flag.svg}} [[Kata'ib Hezbollah]]\n |date          = {{Start date|2019|12|29|df=y}}\n |time          = 11:00 am ([[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]) ([[UTC-05:00]])\n |time-begin    = \n |time-end      = \n |timezone      = \n |executed_by   = {{flag|United States}}\n* {{air force|United States}}\n |outcome       = See ''[[#Aftermath|Aftermath]]''\n |casualties    = \n |fatalities    = 19 (Iraq)\n6 (Syria)<ref name=aawsat>{{cite web|url=https://aawsat.com/english/home/article/2058931/iraq-condemns-us-air-strikes-unacceptable-and-dangerous|title=Iraq Condemns US Air Strikes as Unacceptable and Dangerous|website=Asharq AL-awsat}}</ref>\n |injuries      = 55+<ref name=aawsat/>\n |campaignbox   = {{Campaignbox 2019\u201320 Persian Gulf crisis}}{{Campaignbox Iraqi insurgency (2017\u2013present)}}{{Campaignbox Syrian Civil War}}\n}}\nOn 29 December 2019, the [[United States]] conducted airstrikes against [[Kata'ib Hezbollah]]'s weapons depots and command centers in Iraq and Syria, reportedly killing at least 25 militiamen and wounding 55 more. The [[United States Department of Defense|U.S. Department of Defense]] said the operation was in retaliation for repeated attacks on Iraqi military bases hosting [[Operation Inherent Resolve]] (OIR) coalition forces, particularly the 27 December 2019 [[2019 K-1 Airbase Attack|attack]] on a [[Kirkuk Governorate|Kirkuk]] airbase that left an American civilian contractor dead.<ref name=\"ATSD\">{{cite web|url=https://www.defense.gov/Newsroom/Releases/Release/Article/2047960/statement-from-assistant-to-the-secretary-of-defense-jonathan-hoffman/|title=Statement From Assistant to the Secretary of Defense Jonathan Hoffman|website=U.S. DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE}}</ref><ref name=MaraLago/>\n\nKata'ib Hezbollah, a [[Shia Islam|Shi'ite Muslim]] militia which has links to [[Iran]],<ref name=IranLink>{{cite web |url=http://www.euronews.com/2018/08/31/exclusive-iran-moves-missiles-to-iraq-in-warning-to-enemies-sources |title=Iran moves missiles to Iraq in warning to enemies \u2013 sources |publisher=Euronews |accessdate=2 September 2018}}</ref> denied any responsibility for the attacks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/30/world/middleeast/iraq-airstrikes-us-iran-militias.html|title=American Airstrikes Rally Iraqis Against U.S.|first1=Alissa J.|last1=Rubin|first2=Ben|last2=Hubbard|date=December 30, 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> The unilateral U.S. airstrikes were condemned by the Iraqi government, [[Iraqi Armed Forces]] personnel, and Iran, and culminated in the [[Embassy of the United States, Baghdad|U.S. embassy in Baghdad]] being [[Attack on the United States embassy in Baghdad|attacked]] by Iraqi militiamen and their supporters on 31 December 2019. This in turn led to a [[2020 Baghdad International Airport airstrike|U.S. airstrike]] near Baghdad International Airport on 3 January 2020, killing Iranian general [[Qasem Soleimani]] and Iraqi militia commander [[Abu Mahdi al-Muhandis]].\n\n== Background ==\n{{Main|2019\u201320 Persian Gulf crisis|2019 K-1 Airbase Attack}}\nThe United States [[American-led intervention in Iraq (2014\u2013present)|intervened]] in Iraq in 2014 as a part of [[Operation Inherent Resolve]] (OIR), the U.S.-led mission to degrade and combat the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]] (ISIL) terror organization, and have been training and operating alongside Iraqi forces as a part of the anti-ISIL coalition. ISIL was largely beaten back from Iraq in 2017 during the [[Iraqi Civil War (2014\u20132017)|Iraqi Civil War]], with the help of U.S.-backed forces and Sunni and Shia militias. Iran is known to support [[Shia Islam in Iraq|Shia Iraqi]] militias, a number of which are relatively hostile to the U.S. presence in Iraq and the [[Islam in Iraq|Sunni]]-led Iraqi government.<ref name=IranLink/> Tensions rose between [[Iran]] and the U.S. in 2018 when U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] unilaterally pulled out of the [[Iran nuclear deal framework|2015 nuclear deal]] and reimposed sanctions.<ref name=aawsat/>\n\nOn 27 December 2019, the [[K-1 Air Base]] in [[Kirkuk Governorate|Kirkuk province]], Iraq\u2014one of many Iraqi military bases that host Operation Inherent Resolve coalition personnel\u2014was attacked by multiple rockets, killing a U.S. civilian contractor and injuring four U.S. service members and two [[Iraqi security forces]] personnel. The U.S. blamed the Iranian-backed [[Kata'ib Hezbollah]] militia for the attack while the group denied responsibility.<ref name=MaraLago/>\n\nA senior U.S. official said there had been a \"campaign\" of 11 attacks on Iraqi bases hosting OIR personnel in the two months before the 27 December incident, many of which the U.S. attributed to Kata'ib Hezbollah.<ref name=Guardian>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/30/us-airstrikes-iran-tehran-militia-iraq|title=US: strikes on Iran-backed militia a response to 'campaign' of attacks by Tehran|date=30 December 2019|accessdate=1 January 2020|work=The Guardian}}</ref>\n\n== Military strikes ==\n[[File:DVIDS - Video - US strikes on Kata'ib Hizballah facilities i.webm|thumb|Video of the U.S. strikes on Kata'ib Hezbollah in western Iraq, 29 December 2019]]\nAt around 11:00 am [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]] on 29 December 2019, the United States attacked five [[Kata'ib Hezbollah]] positions in [[Iraq]]i and [[Syria]]n territory. According to the [[The Pentagon|Pentagon]], the U.S. targeted three locations in Iraq and two in Syria, including weapon storage facilities and [[command and control]] posts. One U.S. official claimed the strikes were carried out by [[McDonnell Douglas F-15E Strike Eagle|F-15E]] fighter jets using precision-guided bombs and that secondary explosions were observed after some of the strikes, indicating the sites may have contained ammunition. The ammunition facilities held both rockets and drones used by the militia.<ref name=CNN1>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/12/29/politics/us-strikes-iran-backed-militia-facilities-in-iraq-syria/index.html|title=US strikes 5 facilities in Iraq and Syria linked to Iranian-backed militia|work=CNN|date=29 December 2019|accessdate=31 December 2019}}</ref><ref name=NYT>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/29/world/middleeast/us-airstrikes-iran-iraq-syria.html|title=U.S. Launches Airstrikes on Iranian-Backed Forces in Iraq and Syria|work=The New York Times|date=29 December 2019|accessdate=1 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"ATSD\"/><ref name=MaraLago/>\n\nThe U.S. did not specify the locations of the strikes, but one of the Iraqi strikes had reportedly targeted the militia group's headquarters in or near [[al-Qa'im District]] along the western border with Syria. The strikes in Syria took place along the [[Euphrates]] River Valley in the southeast of the country.<ref name=MaraLago/><ref name=NYT/>\n\n=== Casualties ===\nReportedly, at least 25 militia fighters were killed and 55 wounded.<ref name=aawsat/> According to Iraqi security and militia sources, at least four local Kata'ib Hezbollah commanders were among the dead in the Iraqi strikes, including Abu Ali Khazali.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2019/12/29/Iran-allied-militia-leader-Abu-Ali-Madaniya-among-those-killed-in-US-strike-.html|title=Iran-allied militia leader Abu Ali Khazali among those killed in US strike|website=Al Arabiya|date=29 December 2019}}</ref> U.S. officials could not confirm the militia casualty counts.<ref name=MaraLago/>\n\n== Aftermath ==\n[[File:Secretary of State Pompeo, Secretary of Defense Esper, and Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff Gen. Milley Address Reporters (49328112778).jpg|thumb|U.S. Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]], Secretary of Defense [[Mark Esper]], and Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff Gen. [[Mark A. Milley|Mark Milley]] brief reporters on the airstrikes, 29 December 2019]]\nFollowing the strikes on 29 December, U.S. officials warned that further actions could be undertaken to defend U.S. interests and \"deter further bad behavior from militia groups or from Iran\". U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] was briefed before and after the strikes by his national security advisors and was informed that a further military response could be warranted.<ref name=CNN1/><ref name=MaraLago>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iraq-security-usa/trump-aides-call-u-s-strikes-on-iraq-and-syria-successful-warn-of-potential-further-action-idUSKBN1YX0GR|title=Trump aides call U.S. strikes on Iraq and Syria 'successful,' warn of potential further action|date=29 December 2019|accessdate=31 December 2019|work=Reuters}}</ref>\n\nIn a statement, U.S. [[Assistant to the Secretary of Defense for Public Affairs|Assistant to the Secretary of Defense]] Jonathan Hoffman called the strikes \"defensive\" and stated that they were in retaliation to prior Kata'ib Hezbollah attacks on both Operation Inherent Resolve coalition forces and their Iraqi partners in prior weeks and months. Hoffman also asserted that the militia has received weapons from Iran's [[Quds Force]] that have been used to attack OIR forces.<ref name=ATSD/> U.S. Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]] considered the attacks a warning against any actions by Iran that endangers the lives of Americans.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.france24.com/en/20191229-us-bombs-militant-group-in-iraq-syria-in-retaliation-for-contractor-s-killing |title= US bombs pro-Iran militant group in Iraq, Syria in retaliation for rocket attack. |}}</ref>\n\n=== Reactions in Iraq ===\nAn [[Iraqi Armed Forces]] spokesman stated that U.S. Defense Secretary [[Mark Esper]] informed Iraqi Prime Minister [[Adil Abdul-Mahdi]] half an hour before the operation, to which he strongly objected to and condemned; the spokesman called the unilateral U.S. airstrikes \"a treacherous stab in the back\".<ref name=CNN1/> Prime Minister Abdul-Mahdi later declared three [[day of national mourning|days of national mourning]], from 31 December 2019 until 2 January 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.masrawy.com/news/news_publicaffairs/details/2019/12/31/1697719/\u062d\u062f\u0627\u062f-\u0631\u0633\u0645\u064a-\u0641\u064a-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642-\u0639\u0644\u0649-\u0636\u062d\u0627\u064a\u0627-\u0627\u0644\u063a\u0627\u0631\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u0623\u0645\u0631\u064a\u0643\u064a\u0629|title=\u062d\u062f\u0627\u062f \u0631\u0633\u0645\u064a \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0636\u062d\u0627\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u063a\u0627\u0631\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0645\u0631\u064a\u0643\u064a\u0629|website=\u0645\u0635\u0631\u0627\u0648\u064a.\u0643\u0648\u0645|access-date=2020-01-01}}</ref><ref name=aawsat/> The Prime Minister argued that the attack did not take place based on evidence of a specific threat but was instead [[Geopolitics|geopolitically]] motivated by the tensions between Iran and the U.S.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.net/news/politics/2019/12/31/\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642-\u0627\u0644\u062d\u0634\u062f-\u0627\u0644\u0634\u0639\u0628\u064a-\u0627\u062d\u062a\u062c\u0627\u062c\u0627\u062a-\u0639\u0628\u062f-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0647\u062f\u064a-\u0627\u0644\u0648\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u062a\u062d\u062f\u0629|title=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642.. \u0627\u062d\u062a\u062c\u0627\u062c\u0627\u062a \u0636\u062f \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0641 \"\u0627\u0644\u062d\u0634\u062f\" \u0648\u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0647\u062f\u064a \u064a\u0647\u062f\u062f \u0628\u0645\u0631\u0627\u062c\u0639\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0629 \u0645\u0639 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u062d\u0627\u0644\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0648\u0644\u064a|website=www.aljazeera.net|language=ar|access-date=2020-01-01}}</ref>\n\nSenior [[Popular Mobilization Forces|Popular Mobilization Units]] commander Jamal Jaafar Ibrahimi said \"Our response will be very tough on the American forces in Iraq\".<ref name=aawsat/> \n\n==== U.S. embassy attack ====\n{{Main|Attack on the United States embassy in Baghdad}}\nOn 31 December, PMU militiamen and their supporters attacked the [[Embassy of the United States, Baghdad|U.S. Embassy in Baghdad]], prompting the U.S. to deploy additional soldiers to help quell the situation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/iraq-us-embassy-shooting-baghdad-iran-airstrikes-protest-a9265221.html|title=Iraqi protesters break down gate and storm US embassy as gunshots ring out|date=December 31, 2019|website=The Independent}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/75228a8a607a44863b57021ac33264dc|title=Militiamen breach US Embassy in Baghdad; Trump blames Iran|date=December 31, 2019|website=AP NEWS}}</ref>\n\n=== Other reactions ===\n* {{flag|Iran}} - Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman [[Abbas Mousavi]] said that the U.S. has \"openly shown its support to terrorism and shown its negligence to the independence and national sovereignty of countries\". He added that the U.S. must accept responsibility of the consequences of the \"illegal attacks\".<ref name=CNN2>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/12/30/middleeast/iraq-us-airstrikes-reaction-intl/index.html|title=Iran warns of 'consequences' after US strikes in Iraq and Syria|date=30 December 2019|accessdate=31 December 2019|work=CNN}}</ref> In response to U.S. assertions that Iran was behind the Iraqi airbase attacks, the supreme leader of Iran [[Twitter|tweeted]] \"If Iran wants to fight a country, it will strike directly.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Khamenei_fa/status/1212299106321870848|title=\u0645\u06cc\u0628\u06cc\u0646\u06cc\u062f \u0633\u0631\u0627\u0633\u0631 \u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642 \u0647\u06cc\u062c\u0627\u0646 \u0636\u062f\u0622\u0645\u0631\u06cc\u06a9\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u0686\u0642\u062f\u0631 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u061f \u0628\u0627\u0632 \u0622\u0646 \u062c\u0646\u0627\u0628 \u062a\u0648\u06cc\u06cc\u062a \u06a9\u0631\u062f\u0647 \u06a9\u0647 \u0645\u0627\u0627\u06cc\u0646 \u0631\u0627 \u0627\u0632 \u0686\u0634\u0645 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0645\u06cc\u200c\u0628\u06cc\u0646\u06cc\u0645. \u0634\u0645\u0627 \u063a\u0644\u0637 \u0645\u06cc\u06a9\u0646\u06cc\u062f! \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u06af\u0631\u0628\u062e\u0648\u0627\u0647\u062f\u0628\u0627\u06a9\u0634\u0648\u0631\u06cc \u0645\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0632\u0647 \u06a9\u0646\u062f\u0635\u0631\u06cc\u062d \u0627\u06cc\u0646 \u06a9\u0627\u0631\u0631\u0627 \u0645\u06cc\u06a9\u0646\u062f.\u0645\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u0645\u0646\u0627\u0641\u0639 \u0648 \u0639\u0632\u062a \u0645\u0644\u062a\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u067e\u0627\u06cc\u0628\u0646\u062f\u06cc\u0645 \u0648\u0647\u0631\u06a9\u0633 \u0622\u0646 \u0631\u0627 \u062a\u0647\u062f\u06cc\u062f \u06a9\u0646\u062f \u0628\u062f\u0648\u0646 \u0647\u06cc\u0686 \u0645\u0644\u0627\u062d\u0638\u0647\u200c\u0627\u06cc \u0628\u0627\u0627\u0648 \u0631\u0648\u0628\u0631\u0648 \u0645\u06cc\u0634\u0648\u06cc\u0645 \u0648\u0636\u0631\u0628\u0647 \u0645\u06cc\u0632\u0646\u06cc\u0645.|last=\u0641\u0627\u0631\u0633\u06cc|first=KHAMENEI IR {{!}}|date=2020-01-01|website=@Khamenei_fa|language=fa|access-date=2020-01-01}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Bahrain}} - Bahrain's Foreign Ministry released a statement supporting the airstrike.<ref>{{cite news |title=Bahrain expresses support for U.S. strikes on Kataib Hizbollah facilities in Iraq, Syria: statement |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iraq-security-usa-bahrain/bahrain-expresses-support-for-us-strikes-on-kataib-hizbollah-facilities-in-iraq-syria-statement-idUSKBN1YY003 |accessdate=30 December 2019 |work=Reuters |date=30 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Israel}} - Israeli Prime Minister [[Benjamin Netanyahu]] praised the airstrikes against the militia and emphasized the group's ties to Iran.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jpost.com/Breaking-News/Prime-Minister-Netanyahu-congratulates-Mike-Pompeo-on-US-attacks-in-Iraq-612564|title=Prime Minister Netanyahu congratulates Mike Pompeo on US attacks in Iraq|website=The Jerusalem Post &#124; JPost.com}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Russia}} - Russia\u2019s foreign ministry called the situation unacceptable and called for restraint from both sides.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog_entry/russia-denounces-us-airstrikes-hezbollah-attacks-in-iraq/|title=Russia denounces US airstrikes, Hezbollah attacks in Iraq|website=www.timesofisrael.com}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Hezbollah}} - In a statement, Lebanon's Hezbollah called the attack \"a blatant violation on the sovereignty, security and stability of Iraq and the Iraqi people\".<ref name=CNN2/>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Iranian involvement in the Syrian Civil War]]\n* [[Iraqi protests (2019\u2013present)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2019 airstrikes]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 Persian Gulf crisis]]\n[[Category:American airstrikes during the Syrian Civil War]]\n[[Category:Attacks in Asia in 2019]]\n[[Category:December 2019 events in Syria]]\n[[Category:December 2019 events in Iraq]]\n[[Category:Iran\u2013United States military relations]]\n[[Category:Military operations involving the United States]]\n[[Category:Operation Inherent Resolve]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Short description|War event against Iraqi group Kata'ib Hezbollah}}\n{{Infobox military operation\n |name          = December 2019 United States airstrikes in Iraq and Syria\n |partof        = the American-led interventions [[American-led intervention in Iraq (2014\u2013present)|in Iraq]] and [[American-led intervention in the Syrian Civil War|Syria]] ([[Operation Inherent Resolve]]) and the [[2019\u201320 Persian Gulf crisis]]\n |image         = \n |image_upright = \n |alt           = \n |caption       = \n |scope         = \n |type          = [[Airstrike]]s\n| location  = [[Al Anbar Governorate|Anbar]] and [[Kirkuk Governorate|Kirkuk]], Iraq\n| location2 = Valley of [[Euphrates River]], Syria<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/29/world/middleeast/us-airstrikes-iran-iraq-syria.html U.S. Launches Airstrikes on Iranian-Backed Forces in Iraq and Syria] en: ''[[The New York Times]]''. Consultado el 29-12-2019.</ref>\n |coordinates   = \n |map_type      = \n |map_size      = \n |map_caption   = \n |map_label     = \n |planned       = \n |planned_by    = \n |commanded_by  = \n |objective     = \n |target        = {{flagicon image|Kata'ib Hezbollah flag.svg}} [[Kata'ib Hezbollah]]\n |date          = {{Start date|2019|12|29|df=y}}\n |time          = 11:00 am ([[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]) ([[UTC-05:00]])\n |time-begin    = \n |time-end      = \n |timezone      = \n |executed_by   = {{flag|United States}}\n* {{air force|United States}}\